To properly preserve a testicular biopsy specimen, use 10% formalin as it fixes cells and prevents degradation essential for accurate pathological assessment by the pathologist. This ensures that when sent to them, the integrity of the tissues remains intact allowing precise diagnosis. \boxed{} Agent2’s summary focuses on using 10% formalin to preserve the testicular biopsy specimen effectively so that its structure can be accurately assessed later by the pathologist:

To ensure optimal preservation of the testicular biopsy specimen for subsequent pathology evaluation, place it in 10% formalin which maintains cell structure crucial for diagnostic accuracy. 
